verses.text:
But
if ye turn unto me, and keep my commandments, and do them; though there were of you cast out unto the uttermost part of the heaven,
yet will I gather them from thence, and will bring them unto the place that I have chosen to set my name there.

Yea, when they had made them a molten calf, and said, This
is
 thy God that brought thee up out of Egypt, and had wrought great provocations;

And the other
company of them that gave thanks went over against
them, and I after them, and the half of the people upon the wall, from beyond the tower of the furnaces even unto the broad wall;
